	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002037_0001"><!--pb/@n='69r'--></pb>
				<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName>Hamilton</placeName> <date when="1864-08-04">4<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Aug</abbr><expan>August</expan></choice></date></p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><space extent="1" unit="words"/><date>1864</date></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Dear <persName><choice><abbr>HW</abbr><expan>Horace Waller</expan></choice></persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">All right --- 
<lb/><persName><choice><abbr>Col.</abbr><expan>Colonel</expan></choice> Sabine</persName>'s box goes 
<lb/>to him of course 
<lb/>he being the owner</p>
<lb/><p>Boys better 
<lb/>where they are - 
<lb/>Tell Miss <persName>Mackenzie</persName>
<lb/>that I shall call 
<lb/>as soon as I can 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002037_0002"><!--pb/@n='69v'--></pb>
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">s</hi> Halcome</persName> idem - 
<lb/>- Not at present 
<lb/>- Thanks</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Thus have I 
<lb/>imitated the fast 
<lb/>young man style 
<lb/>though faintly 
<lb/>but under your 
<lb/>judicious training 
<lb/>I may improve</p>
<lb/><p><choice><abbr>Tl</abbr><expan>Truly</expan></choice> Yours</p>
				<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><persName><choice><abbr>DL.</abbr><expan>David Livingstone</expan></choice></persName></p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002037_0003"><!--pb/@n='70r'--></pb><!-- Page completely blank HB 7/1/12 -->

